Excellent non-traditional recipe with good flavor.

@Rachael
I am a professional chef, and did part of my apprenticeship under a true butcher, and there exists no cut of beef called "London Broil", check your NAMP guide. London Broil is a very classic dish made with flank steak, as called for in this recipe. The "London Broil" you refer to, is an invented supermarket cut designed to get rid of hard to sell inferior cuts of beef.
